name: Air Canada New Livery 787-8 [C-GHPQ] Dusk Takeoff from Calgary Airport ᴴᴰ
description:
Air Canada's 787 with the new livery has only been to YYC twice since it's unveiling. We won't have another chance to see it until June when our daily flight to Tokyo is changed to a 788 for the peak summer season (this flight has since been changed to a 789). Here's the second visit of the new livery on the Dreamliner departing off to LHR a couple weeks ago. ATC is included, enjoy!

Thanks for watching!
